obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (41088)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41088&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The manner of appointment and powers and duties of the other officers of the`
  line `University shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (41089)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Authorities of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41089&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be the authorities of the University:--`
  line
  line `(1) the Court;`
  line
  line `(2) the Executive Council;`
  line
  line `(3) the Academic Council;`
  line
  line `(4) the College Development Council;`
  line
  line `(5) the Board of Studies;`
  line
  line `(6) the Finance Committee; and`
  line
  line `(7) such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the`
  line University.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (41090)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `The Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41090&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The constitution of the Court and the term of office of its members shall be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Court shall have the following powers and functions,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to review, from time to time, the broad policies and programmes of the University and to`
  line `suggest measures for the improvement and development of the University;`
  line
  line `(b) to consider and pass resolutions on the annual report and the annual accounts of the University`
  line `and the audit report on such accounts;`
  line
  line `(c) to advise the Visitor in respect of any matter which may be referred to it for advice; and`
  line
  line `(d) to perform such other functions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (41091)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `The Executive Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41091&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Executive Council shall be the principal executive body of the`
  line University.
  line
  line `(2) The constitution of the Executive Council, the term of office of its members and its powers and`
  line `functions shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (41092)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `The Academic Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41092&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Academic Council shall be the principal academic body of the`
  line `University and shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, co-ordinate`
  line `and exercise general supervision over the academic policies of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution of the Academic Council, the term of office of its members and its powers and`
  line `functions shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (41093)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `The College Development Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41093&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The College Development Council shall be responsible`
  line `for admitting Colleges to the privileges of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution of the College Development Council, the term of office of its members and its`
  line `powers and functions shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (41094)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `The Boards of Studies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41094&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The constitution, powers and functions of the Boards of Studies shall`
  line `be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (41095)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `The Finance Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41095&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The constitution, powers and functions of the Finance Committee`
  line `shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (41096)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Other authorities of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41096&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The constitution, powers and functions of other`
  line `authorities, as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the University, shall be prescribed`
  line `by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (41097)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Powers to make Statutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41097&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all`
  line `or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) The constitution, powers and functions of authorities and other bodies of the University, as`
  line `may be constituted from time to time.`
  line
  line `(b) The appointment and continuance in office of the members of the said authorities and bodies,`
  line `the filling up of vacancies of members, and all other matters relating to those authorities and other`
  line `bodies for which it may be necessary or desirable to provide;`
  line
  line `(c) The appointment, powers and duties of the officers of the University and their emoluments;`
  line
  line `(d) the appointment of teachers, academic staff and other employees of the University, their`
  line `emoluments and conditions of service;`
  line
  line `(e) the appointment of teachers, academic staff working in any other University or organisation`
  line `for a specific period for undertaking a joint project;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions of service of employees including provisions pension, insurance and provident`
  line `fund, the manner of termination of service and disciplinary action relating to employees of the`
  line University;
  line
  line `(g) the principles governing the seniority of service of the employees of the University;`
  line
  line `(h) the procedure for arbitration in cases of dispute between employees or students and the`
  line University;
  line
  line `(i) the procedure for appeal to the Executive Council by any employee or student against the`
  line `action of any officer or authority of the University;`
  line
  line `(j) the conferment of autonomous status on a College or an Institution or a Department;`
  line
  line `(k) the establishment and abolition of Schools, Departments, Centres, Halls, Colleges and`
  line Institutions;
  line
  line `(l) the conferment of honorary degrees;`
  line
  line `(m) the withdrawal of degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions;`
  line
  line `(n) the conditions under which Colleges and Institutions may be admitted to the privileges of the`
  line `University and the withdrawal of such privileges;`
  line
  line `(o) the management of Colleges and Institutions established by the University;`
  line
  line `(p) the delegation of powers vested in the authorities or officers of the University;`
  line
  line `(q) the maintenance of discipline among the employees and students;`
  line
  line `(r) all other matters which by this Act are to be or may be provided for by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (41098)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Statutes how to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41098&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1)The first Statutes are those set out in the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Council may, from time to time, make new or additional Statutes or may amend or`
  line `repeal the Statutes referred to in sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Executive Council shall not make amend or repeal any Statutes affecting the status,`
  line `powers or constitution of any authority of the University until such authority has been given an`
  line `opportunity of expressing an opinion in writing on the proposed changes, and any opinion so expressed`
  line `shall be considered by the Executive Council.`
  line
  line `(3) Every new Statute or addition to the Statutes or any amendment or repeal of a Statute shall require`
  line `the assent of the Visitor who may assent thereto or withhold assent or remit to the Executive Council for`
  line re-consideration.
  line
  line `(4) A new Statute or a Statute amending or repealing an existing Statute shall have no validity unless`
  line `it has been assented to by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing sub-sections, the Visitor may make new or`
  line `additional Statutes or amend or repeal the Statutes referred to in sub-section (1), during the period of three`
  line `years immediately after the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `Provided that the Visitor may, on the expiry of the said period of three years, make, within one year`
  line `from the date of such expiry, such detailed Statutes as he may consider necessary and such detailed`
  line `Statutes shall be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing sub-sections, the Visitor may direct the`
  line `University to make provisions in the Statutes in respect of any matter specified by him and if the`
  line `Executive Council is unable to implement such direction within sixty days of its receipt, the Visitor may,`
  line `after considering the reasons, if any, communicated by the Executive Council for its inability to comply`
  line `with such direction, make or amend the Statutes suitably.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (41099)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to make Ordinances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41099&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the`
  line `Ordinances may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of students to the University and their enrolment as such;`
  line
  line `(b) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees, diplomas and certificates of the`
  line University;
  line
  line `(c) the medium of instruction and examination;`
  line
  line `(d) the award of degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions, qualifications for`
  line `the same and the means to be taken relating to the granting and obtaining of the same;`
  line
  line `(e) the fees to be charged for courses of study in the University and for admission to the`
  line `examinations, degrees and diplomas of the University;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions for award of fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(g) the conduct of examinations, including the term of office and manner of appointment and the`
  line `duties of examining bodies, examiners and moderators;`
  line
  line `(h) the conditions of residence of the students of the University;`
  line
  line `(i) the special arrangements, if any, which may be made for the residence, discipline and teaching`
  line `of women students and the prescribing of special courses of studies of them;`
  line
  line `(j) the establishment of Centres of Studies, Boards of Studies, Specialised Laboratories and other`
  line Committees;
  line
  line `(k) the manner of co-operation and collaboration with other Universities, institutions and other`
  line `agencies including learned bodies or associations;`
  line
  line `(l) the creation, composition and functions of any other body which is considered necessary for`
  line `improving the academic life of the University;`
  line
  line `(m) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, studentship, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(n) the supervision of management of Colleges and Institutions admitted to the privileges of the`
  line University;
  line
  line `(o) the setting up of a machinery for redressal or grievances of employees; and`
  line
  line `(p) all other matters which by this Act or the Statutes, are to be or may be, provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
  line
  line `(2) The first Ordinances shall be made by the Vice-Chancellor with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government and the Ordinances so made may be amended, repealed or added to at any time by`
  line `the Executive Council in the manner prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (41100)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title Regulations.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41100&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The authorities of the University may make Regulations, consistent with this Act,`
  line `the Statutes and the Ordinances for the conduct of their own business and that of the Committees, if any,`
  line `appointed by them and not provided for by this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances, in the manner`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (41101)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41101&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual report of the University shall be prepared under the direction of`
  line `the Executive Council, which shall include, among other matters, the steps taken by the University`
  line `towards the fulfilment of its objects and shall be submitted to the Court on or after such date as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes and the Court shall consider the report in its annual meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court shall submit the annual report to the Visitor along with its comments, if any.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the annual report, as prepared under sub-section (1), shall also be submitted to the`
  line `Central Government, which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before both Houses of`
  line Parliament.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (41102)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Annual accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41102&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual accounts and balance-sheet of the University shall be`
  line `prepared under the directions of the Executive Council and shall, once at least every year and at intervals`
  line `of not more than fifteen months, be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or by such`
  line `persons as he may authorise in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the annual accounts together with the audit report thereon shall be submitted to the`
  line `Court and the Visitor along with the observations of the Executive Council.`
  line
  line `(3) Any observations made by the Visitor on the annual accounts shall be brought to the notice of the`
  line `Court and the observations of the Court, if any, shall, after being considered by the Executive Council, be`
  line `submitted to the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of the annual accounts together with the audit report as submitted to the Visitor, shall also`
  line `be submitted to the Central Government, which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before`
  line `both Houses of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(5) The audited annual accounts after having been laid before both Houses of Parliament shall be`
  line `published in the Gazette of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (41103)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Returns and information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41103&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The University shall furnish to the Central Government such returns`
  line `or other information with respect to its property or activities as the Central Government may, from time to`
  line `time, require.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (41104)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Transfer of services of certain employees of the North-Eastern Hill University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41104&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `person who, immediately before the commencement of this Act, is holding or discharging the duties of`
  line `any post or office in connection with the affairs of the North-Eastern Hill University in any area which on`
  line `that date falls within the State of Mizoram shall be deemed to have been transferred to the services of the`
  line `Mizoram University on the same terms and conditions and to the same rights and privileges as to pension,`
  line `gratuity, provident fund and other matters as he would have been had under the North-Eastern Hill`
  line `University Act, 1973 (24 of 1973).`
  line
  line `(2) Any dispute between a person referred to in sub-section (1) and the University shall, at the request`
  line `of such, person, be referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration and the provisions of sub-sections (2),(3),(4) and`
  line `(5) of section 34 shall, as far as may be, apply to a reference made under this sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (41105)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Conditions of service of employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41105&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every employee of the University shall be appointed`
  line `under a written contract, which shall be lodged with the University and a copy of which shall be furnished`
  line `to the employee concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any dispute arising out of the contract between the University and any employee shall, at the`
  line `request of the employee, be referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by`
  line `the Executive Council, one member nominated by the employee concerned and an empire appointed by`
  line `the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Tribunal shall be final, and no suit shall lie in any civil court in respect of the`
  line `matters decided by the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) Every request made by the employee under sub-section (2), shall be deemed to be a submission to`
  line `arbitration upon the terms of this section within the meaning of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996`
  line `(26 of 1996).`
  line
  line `(5) The procedure for regulating the work of the Tribunal shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (41106)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Procedure of appeal and arbitration in disciplinary cases against students.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41106&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any student`
  line `or candidate for an examination whose name has been removed from the rolls of the University by the`
  line `orders or resolution of the Vice-Chancellor, Discipline Committee or Examination Committee, as the case`
  line `may be, and who has been debarred from appearing at the examinations of the University for more than`
  line `one year, may, within ten days of the date of receipt of such orders or copy of such resolution by him,`
  line `appeal to the Executive Council and the Executive Council may confirm, modify or reverse the decision`
  line `of the Vice-Chancellor or the Committee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Any dispute arising out of any disciplinary action taken by the University against a student shall,`
  line `at the request of such student, be referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration and the provisions of sub-sections`
  line `(2), (3), (4) and (5) of section 34 shall, as far as may be, apply to a reference made under this sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (41107)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `Right to appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41107&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Every employee or student of the University or of a College or Institution`
  line `maintained by the University or admitted to its privileges shall, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Act, have a right to appeal within such time as may be prescribed by the Statutes, to the Executive`
  line `Council against the decision of any officer or authority of the University or of the Principal or the`
  line `management of any College or an Institution, as the case may be, and thereupon the Executive Council`
  line `may confirm, modify or reverse the decision appealed against.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (41108)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title `Provident and pension funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41108&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1)The University shall constitute for the benefit of its`
  line `employees such provident or pension fund or provide such insurance schemes as it may deem fit in such`
  line `manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such provident fund or pension fund has been so constituted, the Central Government may`
  line `declare that the provisions of the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (28 of 1925), shall apply to such fund, as if it`
  line `were a Government provident fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (41109)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 39
  title `Disputes as to constitution of University authorities and bodies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41109&sectionno=38&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `If any question arises as to`
  line `whether any person has been duly elected or appointed as, or is entitled to be, a member of any authority`
  line `or other body of the University, the matter shall be referred to the Visitor whose decision thereon shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (41110)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 40
  title `Filling of casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41110&sectionno=39&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `All casual vacancies among the members (other than ex officio`
  line `members) of any authority or other body of the University shall be filled, as soon as may be, by the`
  line `person or body who appoints, elects or co-opts the member whose place has become vacant and person`
  line `appointed, elected or co-opted to a casual vacancy shall be a member of such authority or body for the`
  line `residue of the term for which the person whose place he fills would have been a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (41111)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 41
  title `Proceedings of University authorities or bodies not invalidated by vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41111&sectionno=40&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `No act or`
  line `proceedings of any authority or other body of the University shall be invalid merely by reason of the`
  line `existence of a vacancy or vacancies among its members.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (41112)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 42
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41112&sectionno=41&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against`
  line `any officer or other employee of the University for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be`
  line `done in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (41113)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 43
  title `Mode of proof of University record.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41113&sectionno=42&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `A copy of any receipt, application, notice, order,`
  line `proceeding, resolution of any authority or Committee of the University, or other documents in possession`
  line `of the University, or any entry in any register duly maintained by the University, if certified by the`
  line `Registrar, shall be received as prima facie evidence of such receipt, application, notice, order, proceeding,`
  line `resolution, or documents or the existence of entry in the register and shall be admitted as evidence of the`
  line `matters and transactions therein where the original thereof would, if produced, have been admissible in`
  line `evidence, notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (41114)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41114&sectionno=43&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (41115)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 45
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41115&sectionno=44&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act and the Statutes:--`
  line
  line `(a) the first Vice-Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor in such manner and on such`
  line `conditions as may be deemed fit and each of the said officer shall hold office for such term, not`
  line `exceeding five years as may be specified by the Visitor;`
  line
  line `(b) the first Registrar and the first Finance Officer shall be appointed by the Visitor and each of`
  line `the said officers shall hold office for a term of three years;`
  line
  line `(c) the first Court and the first Executive Council shall consist of not more than thirty members`
  line `and eleven members, respectively, who shall be nominated by the Visitor and shall hold office for a`
  line `term of three years;`
  line
  line `(d) the first College Development Council shall consist of not more than ten members, who shall`
  line `be nominated by the Visitor and they shall hold office for a term of three years;`
  line
  line `(e) the first Academic Council shall consist of not more than twenty-one members, who shall be`
  line `nominated by the Visitor and they shall hold office for a term of three years:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any vacancy occurs in the above offices or authorities, the same shall be filled by`
  line `appointment or nomination, as the case may be, by the Visitor, and the person so appointed or`
  line `nominated shall hold office for so long as the officer or member in whose place he is appointed or`
  line `nominated would have held office, if such vacancy had not occurred.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (41116)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 46
  title `Completion of courses of studies in Colleges or Institutions affiliated to the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41116&sectionno=45&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, or in the Statutes or the Ordinances, any student of a`
  line `College, Institution, School or Department, who, immediately before the admission of such College,`
  line `Institution, School or Department, to the privileges of the University, was studying for a degree, diploma`
  line `or certificate of the North-Eastern Hill University, shall be permitted by the University, to complete his`
  line `course for that degree, diploma or certificate, as the case may be, and the Mizoram University and such`
  line `College, Institution, School or Department, shall provide for the instructions and examination of such`
  line `student in accordance with the syllabus of studies of the North Eastern Hill University.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (41117)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 47
  title `Statutes, Ordinances and Regulations to be published in the Official Gazette and to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41117&sectionno=46&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be published`
  line `in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation or both Houses agree that the Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation should not be made, the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation shall thereafter have`
  line `effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that Statute, Ordinance or Regulation.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make Statutes, Ordinances or Regulations shall include the power to give`
  line `retrospective effect from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act, to the Statutes,`
  line `Ordinances or Regulations or any of them but no retrospective effect shall be given to any Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation so as to prejudicially affect the interests of any person to whom such Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation may be applicable.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (41118)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 48
  title `Amendment of Act 24 of 1973.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818&sectionId=41118&sectionno=47&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00011_200008_1517807323818
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `In the North-Eastern Hill University Act, 1973,--`
  line
  line `(i) in section 1, in sub-section (2), for the words "Union Territories of Arunachal Pradesh and`
  line `Mizoram", the words "State of Arunachal Pradesh" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in section 2, in clause (l), for the words "Union territories of Arunachal Pradesh and`
  line `Mizoram", the words "State of Arunachal Pradesh" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(iii) in section 6, in sub-section (1), for the words "Union territories of Arunachal Pradesh and`
  line `Mizoram", the words "State of Arunachal Pradesh" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
